<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="M" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Moist1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Moist,</orth> adj. moderately wet, damp: <cit><quote>my smooth m. hand,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 143" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 143</bibl></cit>. cf. <bibl n="shak. oth 3.4.36" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. III, 4, 36</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 3.4.36" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. III, 4, 36</bibl> <emph>his</emph> (the lark's) <cit><quote>m. cabinet,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 854" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 854</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>m. Hesperus,</quote> <bibl n="shak. aww 2.1.167" default="NO" valid="yes">All's II, 1, 167</bibl></cit>; cf. <emph>the m. star</emph> (the moon) <bibl n="shak. ham 1.1.118" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 1, 118</bibl>. <emph>a m. eye</emph> (a sign of old age) <bibl n="shak. 2h4 1.2.203" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B I, 2, 203</bibl>. <emph>m. impediments</emph> (tears) <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.5.140" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 5, 140</bibl>. <cit><quote>m. eyes,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.1.49" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 1, 49</bibl></cit>. <emph>the two m. elements</emph> (water and air) <bibl n="shak. tro 1.3.41" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. I, 3, 41</bibl>. <cit><quote>these m. trees,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tim 4.3.223" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 3, 223</bibl></cit> (many M. Edd. unnecessarily <emph>mossed</emph>).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>